Package: siapopr
Type: Package
Title: siapopr is an R implementation of SIApop to simulate infinite-allele
    branching process populations
Version: 0.0.1
Author: Ollie McDonald and Franziska Michor
Maintainer: Ollie McDonald <mcdonald@jimmy.harvard.edu>
Description: siapopr is a branching process simulation software written in
    C++ to simulate birth-death-mutation processes where each new mutation
    is unique, following the infinite-allele assumption.
License: GPL-3
LazyData: TRUE
Imports:
    Rcpp,
    RcppGSL,
    igraph,
    ggplot2,
    dplyr,
    tidyr
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppGSL
SystemRequirements: GNU GSL
NeedsCompilation: yes
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
URL: https://github.com/olliemcdonald/siapopr
BugReports: https://github.com/olliemcdonald/siapopr/issues
